post_text:
COVID-19 Update:

As stated on Wednesday, August 12, 2020 one of the staff members at Canton Harbor had tested positive for COVID-19 on Wednesday, August 11. In the conversations that followed with the local health department and the administrative team, Canton Harbor High School has made the decision to DELAY the start of the school to August 31. The original start date was scheduled for August 26. Any parent/student that has scheduled a date and time for orientation starting August 18, will be called to reschedule their appointment. The new orientation dates will begin on Monday, August 24, 2020. Thank you for your understanding and flexibility during this this time of unknowns and challenges.

The new orientation dates will begin on Monday, August 24, 2020. Thank you for your understanding and flexibility during this this time of unknowns and challenges.

post_text:
Attention Covid-19 Update:

One of our staff members has tested positive for Covid-19. We will be shutting down the building to clean. The earliest the building will reopen is Monday. Our staff is continuing to work from home. If you have any questions please feel free to reach out. Thank you.

post_text:
Canton Harbor will begin the 2020-2021 School Year VIRTUALLY. Please review the documents below as they provide key information about the virtual opening of the school year.

Information regarding student & parent orientation is contained within these documents. Students and (1) Parent/Guardian must call to set up an orientation appointment. Orientation dates are August 18, 19, 20, 24, 25.

If you have any questions please feel free to call Canton Harbor at 330-452-8414; Monday-Thursday from 9a-2p. This same information can be accessed on our website, www.cantonharbor.org.

post_text: Canton Harbor's Restart Plan is coming soon. Our team is in the final stages of putting together our plan for the upcoming school year. An announcement regarding the final Restart Plan will be available by the end of the day on Wednesday, July 29, 2020. Thank for your patience, understanding, and flexibility as we work to create the safest learning environment for our students, staff, families, and community. Please be sure to check our Facebook page and/or our website, www.cantonharbor.org for updates.

If you need help jump into the Google Meets Sessions with your teachers or contact them directly...Google Classroom, Facebook, email, Google Voice, etc. I want to order Caps, Gowns, and Diplomas, but is on you to determine how many I need to order!

14 School Days, Students! Only 14 School Days to get your work completed so you can earn the most credits possible this year! You can do anything for 14 days. Your teachers are available, PLEASE contact them, attend their Google Meets Sessions, and COMPLETE THE WORK!

Underclassman- Continue to make moves this year so you are in a good position next year! Earn as much credit as you can to keep moving forward!

Potential Grads- You have to do the work! Make it happen. You are so close to earning your right to graduate from high school! You CAN do this and Canton Harbor has your back to help you through it!

Buckle Down Everyone, May is here...Let the CRUNCH TIME BEGIN!

22 Days Everyone! Twenty-Two Days...Teachers and Staff are working extremely hard to make sure all your work is available to complete and answer any questions you may have. Students, time is ticking by quickly. Use this time wisely to get ahead or make the push to finish!

Underclassman- Take this time to make a push to finish any class(es) that you are close to finishing; keep earning credits and moving closer to graduation. Don't wait until next year to get it done. Make it happen in the next 22 Days!

We understand this may be a difficult time to navigate. Canton Harbor wants to continue to provide you with resources to get your best each day. Restoration Community Services started providing school-based mental health services for students at Canton Harbor High School back in January. We are pleased to announce those services will continue during our extended school closure. I have provided Ms Charolotte and Ms. Dawn’s contact information below in case you need them. We are all here to support you!

Both Ms. Charlotte and Ms. Dawn are available from 8a to 3p

Ms. Charlotte will be available on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday.
Ms Charlotte’s RCS phone number is:
+1 (234) 228-7827
Email: calw.RCS@gmail.com

Ms. Dawn will be available Monday and Friday
Ms. Dawn’s RCS phone number is:
+1 (330) 938-8443
Email: rcommunityservices@gmail.com

post_text:
Parents, guardians, and students of Canton Harbor High School. In response to Governor Mike DeWine and the States Health Officials press conference this afternoon related to the prevention of COVID-19, or the Coronavirus, Canton Harbor High School’s administrative team will be working to put a plan of action in place for the upcoming weeks. The plan will be in line with recommendations from the State Health Department.

More information on Canton Harbor High School’s plan will be available by tomorrow afternoon. You will receive a full disclosure of Canton Harbor High School’s plan through our website and other social media outlets. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation as we continue to move forward.
